Yesterday, I decided I was going to finish my 5th shawl quest.  I have been working hard on all my trade skills, spending tons of time and pp to get them to the appropriate levels for the quest.  Of the 75 threads needed from Velks, I only needed 30 more.  So I head to Velks with a friend and we get a group.  I immediately make it known that the only loot I would like is the threads for my quest.  The only other person in the group who needs them is a shaman.  We agree to share even though he isnt even working on his shawls yet.  No problem, I can share.  After awhile, he leaves and we have a Mage join us.  Again, I mention right away that I am only interested in the threads (I need 24 more at this point). The mage says she also needs threads, so again, we agree to share.  This works fine.  Once she loots 5 threads, she combines them and fails.  Then it happens again.  Trying to be helpful, I ask what her tailoring skill is.  Her response...40!  Now, Im not sure what exactly the trivial level is for these, but I KNOW its higher than 40.  I tell her this and she says she is using the threads to work up her tailoring skill.  My mouth drops open.  I have spent hours collecting silks and pelts to get my tailoring skill to 135 before I even attempted this part of the quest.  Here sits this mage who is wasting these precious, no drop threads to increase her skill! And to add fuel to the fire, she isnt even up to shawl 5 yet, shes only completed the second.<br>
Needless to say, this upset me greatly.  I have spent many times in Velks before I got to the point where I needed the threads and let others in the group loot them because they were working on that part of the quest.  Collecting 75 threads is so hard, I felt like just ninja looting the threads and being as greedy as this person was.<br>
The good side is that I got my threads and my 5th shawl (yay!).<br>
Sorry for rambling, but I had to get that out.  I feel much better now.<br>
*hugs*<br>
The One and Only Tart <p>Liltart Wydowmaker 55th Druid <br>
